transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra.

Speaker 2: How can I help you?

Speaker 1: I would like to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 2: No problem, I can help you out with that.

Speaker 1: Give me one second.

Speaker 2: All right, David, can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 1: 7-31-1960.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: I see you're a VIP status customer.

Speaker 2: I see the doctor put you on refills every two months,

Speaker 1: which you're not required to have.

Speaker 2: How's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 1: It's not, that's why I wanted to get rid of it.

Speaker 2: Okay, not a problem.

Speaker 1: Do you happen to have the medication on you by chance?

Speaker 2: No.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I think that it looks like the pharmacy

Speaker 1: just sent you regular generic Viagra,

Speaker 2: as you did not receive the AGV.

Speaker 1: What's it do with pharmacy note?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I think they ran out and sent you generics

Speaker 1: and they did not tell us.

Speaker 2: Give me a second, I'm gonna get you out of replacement,

Speaker 1: and then I'm gonna tell you

Speaker 2: how you can confirm you received the correct medication.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Perfect, so I put in this order.

Speaker 2: So when you get this new bottle in the mail in a few days,

Speaker 1: on the bottle it's gonna say AGV,

Speaker 2: but it's also going to say Greenstone.

Speaker 1: And Greenstone is the name of Pfizer's manufacturer in France.

Speaker 2: And then on the pills,

Speaker 1: the only number imprinted on the individual pills

Speaker 2: is going to be the number 50 for the milligrams.

Speaker 1: And those are the two ways you can confirm

Speaker 2: you received the FDA approved Pfizer-Viagra AGV,

Speaker 1: because I believe right now your pills

Speaker 2: have the letter AC imprinted on them,

Speaker 1: followed by the numbers 390 or 340.

Speaker 2: And then on the bottle, it will say APCO.

Speaker 1: So you can just go ahead and throw those in the trash.

Speaker 2: And then I'm gonna pause your refills for six months

Speaker 1: until July 31st, that way,

Speaker 2: because if I cancel out now,

Speaker 1: delete your profile and the pharmacy

Speaker 2: would not be able to send you that replacement.

Speaker 1: And then I'll give you my extension,

Speaker 2: so you can call me back

Speaker 1: and let me know how the AGV works out for you.

Speaker 2: Hello?

Speaker 1: Hi.

Speaker 2: Can you hear me?

Speaker 1: Yep, I heard you.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, I'll give you my name and extension,

Speaker 1: so you can call me back and let me know how it works out.

Speaker 2: My extension is 0020.

Speaker 1: And my name is Michelle.

Speaker 2: All right, perfect.

Speaker 1: You're all set, David.

Speaker 2: I hope you have a great week.

Speaker 1: Bye.
